steps.title: Describe Your Scene
steps.description: Start by describing your scene here. The AI will use this to generate your storyboard panels.

steps.title: Set the Mood and Tone
steps.description: Add a mood or tone to guide the AI for more specific results.

steps.title: Manage Your Cast
steps.description: View and manage the characters available for your project here. These characters can be used in your scene descriptions. Characters you 'select' will be in the panels that are generated.  Only includes characters with meaningful parts in the scene.

steps.title: Select Your Location
steps.description: This is the single most contributing factor to whether or not the scene description, lines and ultimately the generated images line up with the Scene Description.

steps.title: Generate Your Storyboard
steps.description: Once you've described your scene, click here to generate your storyboard panels using AI.

steps.title: Add Panels Manually
steps.description: If you prefer, you can also add blank panels to your storyboard and fill them in yourself.

steps.title: Save and Play Your Story
steps.description: Don't forget to save your project! When ready, click 'Play Movie' to see your storyboard in action.
